Note:
==============================================================================
IEEE 754-2008 binary128 (quadruple precision) software implementation
==============================================================================

Format (128 bits):
  bit 127      : sign
  bits 126-112 : exponent (15 bits, bias 16383)
  bits 111-0   : mantissa fraction (112 bits, implicit leading 1)

Internal representation choice: 16-byte arena-allocated buffer addressed by
pointer. The buffer layout is big-endian-of-words but little-endian-byte
WITHIN each word - i.e. byte offset 0 holds the LOW 64 bits and byte offset
8 holds the HIGH 64 bits. This matches the typical x86-64 SysV ABI mapping
for an _Float128 stored as struct { uint64_t low; uint64_t high; } and is the
same layout used by `softfloat.runa` (see its float128_unpack / float128_pack
helpers). We use this layout so future cross-module use of binary128 values
is byte-compatible. The "high word" carries the sign bit, exponent, and top
48 bits of the mantissa; the "low word" carries the bottom 64 bits.

We chose flat-buffer over a struct-of-limbs because:
  - Runa Type structures are nominal: passing a Type by value requires the
    compiler to materialize each field. A 16-byte buffer addressed by
    pointer fits cleanly into the existing Memory/Arena workflow.
  - bit-pattern interop with softfloat.runa is byte-identical so the two
    modules can interoperate without conversion.

Internal arithmetic uses 256-bit intermediate values for multiplication.
We carry the 256-bit intermediate as four 64-bit limbs in Integer-sized
slots; the high two limbs hold the leading 128 bits of the product and
the low two limbs hold the trailing 128 bits (used for sticky tracking).

References:
  IEEE 754-2008 (full standard)
  Hauser, John R., "SoftFloat Library Release 3e" (Berkeley)
  libquadmath testsuite (used as KAT source where appropriate)
  Goldberg, "What Every Computer Scientist Should Know About Floating-Point"
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/bitwise_core.runa" as Bits
Import "runtime/core/memory/arena.runa" as Arena

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Format constants
Note: ============================================================================

Constant F128_BITS as Integer is 128
Constant F128_EXP_BITS as Integer is 15
Constant F128_MANT_BITS as Integer is 112
Constant F128_BIAS as Integer is 16383
Constant F128_EXP_MAX as Integer is 32767
Constant F128_BYTES as Integer is 16

Note: Within the high word: bit 63 = sign, bits 62..48 = exponent, bits 47..0
Note: = top 48 bits of mantissa.
Constant F128_HIGH_SIGN_MASK as Integer is -9223372036854775808
Constant F128_HIGH_EXP_MASK as Integer is 9223090561878065152
Constant F128_HIGH_MANT_MASK as Integer is 281474976710655
Constant F128_HIDDEN_BIT_HIGH as Integer is 281474976710656

Note: Rounding modes (mirror Float32's set).
Constant ROUND_NEAREST_EVEN as Integer is 0
Constant ROUND_TOWARD_ZERO as Integer is 1
Constant ROUND_TOWARD_POSITIVE as Integer is 2
Constant ROUND_TOWARD_NEGATIVE as Integer is 3

Note: Exception flags.
Constant FLAG_INVALID as Integer is 1
Constant FLAG_DIVIDE_BY_ZERO as Integer is 2
Constant FLAG_OVERFLOW as Integer is 4
Constant FLAG_UNDERFLOW as Integer is 8
Constant FLAG_INEXACT as Integer is 16

Let F128_ROUNDING_MODE be 0
Let F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS be 0

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Allocation
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "f128_alloc" takes arena as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Allocate a 16-byte Float128 in the supplied arena and zero-initialize.
    Caller owns the lifetime through the arena.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    arena_allocate + memory_fill with 0.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Single arena bump + 16-byte zero.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    No buffer is returned uninitialized: zero is a valid Float128 (+0.0).
    @End Security_Scope
    Let p be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, F128_BYTES
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_fill from Memory with p, 0, F128_BYTES
    Return p
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Field access helpers
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "f128_load_high" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Load the high 64-bit word from a Float128 buffer.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    The high word lives at byte offset 8.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Single 64-bit load.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller-owned buffer; no bounds check.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p, 8
End Process

Process called "f128_load_low" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Load the low 64-bit word.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    The low word lives at byte offset 0.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Single 64-bit load.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller-owned buffer.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p, 0
End Process

Process called "f128_store_high" takes p as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Store the high 64-bit word.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Single 64-bit store at offset 8.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One store.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with p, 8, value
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "f128_store_low" takes p as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Store the low 64-bit word.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Single 64-bit store at offset 0.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One store.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with p, 0, value
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "f128_get_sign" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Sign bit is bit 63 of the high word.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Load high, right-shift by 63, mask 1.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load + two ALU ops.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure read.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let hi be proc f128_load_high with p
    Let shifted be hi shifted right by 63
    Return shifted bitwise and 1
End Process

Process called "f128_get_exponent" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    The 15-bit biased exponent occupies bits 62..48 of the high word.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Shift high right by 48, mask with 0x7FFF.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load + two ALU ops.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure read.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let hi be proc f128_load_high with p
    Let shifted be hi shifted right by 48
    Return shifted bitwise and F128_EXP_MAX
End Process

Process called "f128_get_mantissa_high" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    The top 48 bits of the 112-bit mantissa occupy bits 47..0 of the high word.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Load high, AND with mask of low 48 bits.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load + one ALU op.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure read.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let hi be proc f128_load_high with p
    Return hi bitwise and F128_HIGH_MANT_MASK
End Process

Process called "f128_get_mantissa_low" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    The bottom 64 bits of the 112-bit mantissa are exactly the low word.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Load low word.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure read.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return proc f128_load_low with p
End Process

Process called "f128_set_fields" takes p as Integer, sign as Integer, biased_exp as Integer, mant_high_48 as Integer, mant_low_64 as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Compose sign, biased exponent, and the 112-bit mantissa into the high
    and low 64-bit words and store them.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Defensive masking on each field, then pack via shifts and ORs.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller-owned buffer; defensive masking shields against caller passing
    wider values.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let s be sign bitwise and 1
    Let e be biased_exp bitwise and F128_EXP_MAX
    Let mh be mant_high_48 bitwise and F128_HIGH_MANT_MASK
    Let hi be s shifted left by 63
    Let e_shifted be e shifted left by 48
    Set hi to hi bitwise or e_shifted
    Set hi to hi bitwise or mh
    proc f128_store_high with p, hi
    proc f128_store_low with p, mant_low_64
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Classification predicates
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "f128_is_zero" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Both ±0 have all bits except the sign equal to zero.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Load high & low, strip sign, check both are zero.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Two loads, two ALU ops, two branches.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let hi be proc f128_load_high with p
    Let lo be proc f128_load_low with p
    Let hi_no_sign be hi bitwise and 9223372036854775807
    If hi_no_sign is not equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If lo is not equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "f128_is_inf" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Inf has exponent=0x7FFF and mantissa=0.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Check exponent and that mantissa words are all zero.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Two loads, a handful of ALU ops.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let exp be proc f128_get_exponent with p
    If exp is not equal to F128_EXP_MAX:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let mh be proc f128_get_mantissa_high with p
    Let ml be proc f128_get_mantissa_low with p
    If mh is not equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If ml is not equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "f128_is_nan" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    NaN has exponent=0x7FFF and mantissa != 0.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Check exponent and that at least one mantissa word is nonzero.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Two loads, a few branches.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let exp be proc f128_get_exponent with p
    If exp is not equal to F128_EXP_MAX:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let mh be proc f128_get_mantissa_high with p
    If mh is not equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let ml be proc f128_get_mantissa_low with p
    If ml is not equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "f128_is_signaling_nan" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Signaling NaN: NaN with mantissa MSB clear. MSB of 112-bit mantissa
    is bit 47 of the high mantissa word.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Reject non-NaN, then inspect bit 47 of the mantissa high word.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    A few branches.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let nan be proc f128_is_nan with p
    If nan is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let mh be proc f128_get_mantissa_high with p
    Let msb_mask be 140737488355328
    If (mh bitwise and msb_mask) is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "f128_is_subnormal" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Subnormal: exponent==0 and mantissa != 0.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Check exponent==0 then mantissa != 0.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    A few branches.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let exp be proc f128_get_exponent with p
    If exp is not equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let mh be proc f128_get_mantissa_high with p
    If mh is not equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let ml be proc f128_get_mantissa_low with p
    If ml is not equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "f128_is_normal" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Normal: 0 < exponent < 0x7FFF.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Range check on exponent.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load + two branches.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let exp be proc f128_get_exponent with p
    If exp is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If exp is equal to F128_EXP_MAX:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "f128_is_finite" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Finite: exponent != 0x7FFF.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Single comparison.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load + one branch.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let exp be proc f128_get_exponent with p
    If exp is equal to F128_EXP_MAX:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "f128_is_negative" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Sign bit is set.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Read sign bit.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load + two ALU ops.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return proc f128_get_sign with p
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Rounding mode + exception flags
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "f128_set_rounding_mode" takes mode as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Switch the active rounding mode.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Validated store.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Module-global state.
    @End Security_Scope
    If mode is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If mode is greater than 3:
        Return 0
    End If
    Set F128_ROUNDING_MODE to mode
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "f128_get_rounding_mode" returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Read the active rounding mode.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Single load.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Read-only.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return F128_ROUNDING_MODE
End Process

Process called "f128_raise_flag" takes flag as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    OR a flag into the sticky exception register.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Bitwise OR + store.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One ALU + one store.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Module-global mutation.
    @End Security_Scope
    Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or flag
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "f128_clear_flags" returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Reset the sticky exception register.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Single store of 0.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One store.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Module-global mutation.
    @End Security_Scope
    Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to 0
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "f128_get_flags" returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Snapshot of the sticky exception register.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Single load.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One load.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Read-only.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Constructors / special values
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "f128_make_zero" takes arena as Integer, sign as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Construct ±0 in a fresh buffer.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Allocate then write the sign bit if needed.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One alloc + one store.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Buffer owned by arena.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let p be proc f128_alloc with arena
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If sign is equal to 1:
        proc f128_store_high with p, F128_HIGH_SIGN_MASK
    End If
    Return p
End Process

Process called "f128_make_inf" takes arena as Integer, sign as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Construct ±Inf in a fresh buffer.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    sign bit | exponent_field_max << 48.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One alloc + one store.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Buffer owned by arena.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let p be proc f128_alloc with arena
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let hi be F128_EXP_MAX shifted left by 48
    If sign is equal to 1:
        Set hi to hi bitwise or F128_HIGH_SIGN_MASK
    End If
    proc f128_store_high with p, hi
    Return p
End Process

Process called "f128_make_qnan" takes arena as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Construct the canonical quiet NaN.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Exponent = 0x7FFF, mantissa MSB = 1, everything else 0.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One alloc + one store.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Buffer owned by arena.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let p be proc f128_alloc with arena
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let exp_part be F128_EXP_MAX shifted left by 48
    Let quiet_bit be 140737488355328
    Let hi be exp_part bitwise or quiet_bit
    proc f128_store_high with p, hi
    Return p
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: 112-bit mantissa arithmetic helpers (pair of 64-bit limbs)
Note: ============================================================================
Note: We split each 112-bit mantissa into (high, low) where high carries the
Note: top 48 bits and low carries the bottom 64. For internal computations we
Note: widen to (high, low) with high carrying up to 64 bits.
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "f128_add128" takes a_hi as Integer, a_lo as Integer, b_hi as Integer, b_lo as Integer, out_hi_ptr as Integer, out_lo_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Sum two 128-bit unsigned values held as (hi, lo) limb pairs.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Add lo limbs; detect carry by checking that result_lo < a_lo (unsigned
    semantics implemented via signed range checks). Add hi limbs + carry.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Two adds + one branch. On x86-64 the obvious lowering is addq + adcq.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure; out pointers are caller-owned.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let lo_sum be a_lo plus b_lo
    Note: Detect unsigned overflow by treating limbs as unsigned 64-bit.
    Note: In two's-complement: a_lo + b_lo overflowed iff
    Note: (a_lo XOR lo_sum) AND (b_lo XOR lo_sum) has bit 63 set.
    Let xor_a be a_lo bitwise xor lo_sum
    Let xor_b be b_lo bitwise xor lo_sum
    Let and_xor be xor_a bitwise and xor_b
    Note: Equivalent unsigned-carry detection: carry iff
    Note: (a_lo & b_lo) | ((a_lo | b_lo) & ~lo_sum) has bit 63 set.
    Let and_lo be a_lo bitwise and b_lo
    Let or_lo be a_lo bitwise or b_lo
    Let not_sum be bitwise not lo_sum
    Let inner be or_lo bitwise and not_sum
    Let carry_marker be and_lo bitwise or inner
    Let carry_marker_shift be carry_marker shifted right by 63
    Let carry be carry_marker_shift bitwise and 1
    Let hi_sum be a_hi plus b_hi
    Set hi_sum to hi_sum plus carry
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_hi_ptr, 0, hi_sum
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_lo_ptr, 0, lo_sum
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "f128_sub128" takes a_hi as Integer, a_lo as Integer, b_hi as Integer, b_lo as Integer, out_hi_ptr as Integer, out_lo_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Subtract one 128-bit value from another, assuming a >= b.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Subtract lo limbs; detect borrow when a_lo < b_lo (unsigned).
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Two subs + one branch.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let lo_diff be a_lo minus b_lo
    Note: Unsigned borrow detection: borrow iff
    Note: ((~a_lo) & b_lo) | (((~a_lo) | b_lo) & lo_diff) has bit 63 set.
    Let not_a be bitwise not a_lo
    Let and_part be not_a bitwise and b_lo
    Let or_part be not_a bitwise or b_lo
    Let inner_b be or_part bitwise and lo_diff
    Let borrow_marker be and_part bitwise or inner_b
    Let borrow_marker_shift be borrow_marker shifted right by 63
    Let borrow be borrow_marker_shift bitwise and 1
    Let hi_diff be a_hi minus b_hi
    Set hi_diff to hi_diff minus borrow
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_hi_ptr, 0, hi_diff
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_lo_ptr, 0, lo_diff
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "f128_compare128" takes a_hi as Integer, a_lo as Integer, b_hi as Integer, b_lo as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Unsigned compare on a 128-bit pair. Returns -1/0/1.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Compare hi limbs first as unsigned by flipping sign bits before
    signed compare, then lo limbs the same way.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    A few branches.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let a_hi_u be a_hi bitwise xor F128_HIGH_SIGN_MASK
    Let b_hi_u be b_hi bitwise xor F128_HIGH_SIGN_MASK
    If a_hi_u is less than b_hi_u:
        Return -1
    End If
    If a_hi_u is greater than b_hi_u:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let a_lo_u be a_lo bitwise xor F128_HIGH_SIGN_MASK
    Let b_lo_u be b_lo bitwise xor F128_HIGH_SIGN_MASK
    If a_lo_u is less than b_lo_u:
        Return -1
    End If
    If a_lo_u is greater than b_lo_u:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "f128_shift_right128_sticky" takes hi as Integer, lo as Integer, count as Integer, out_hi_ptr as Integer, out_lo_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Shift a 128-bit value right by `count`, accumulating shifted-out
    1-bits into a sticky bit (bit 0 of the result low limb).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Bitwise loop. Cap count to 128 to avoid unbounded iteration.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Bounded loop with one OR per iteration.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    If count is less than or equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_hi_ptr, 0, hi
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_lo_ptr, 0, lo
        Return 0
    End If
    Let n be count
    If n is greater than 128:
        Set n to 128
    End If
    Let cur_hi be hi
    Let cur_lo be lo
    Let sticky be 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than n:
        Let lost be cur_lo bitwise and 1
        Set sticky to sticky bitwise or lost
        Note: shift right by 1: low gets (high<<63 | low>>1), high gets logical-shift-right
        Let hi_lowbit be cur_hi bitwise and 1
        Let new_lo_high_part be hi_lowbit shifted left by 63
        Let cur_lo_shifted be cur_lo shifted right by 1
        Note: When right-shifting an unsigned value, we need a logical shift.
        Note: Mask off any sign-extended bits from the arithmetic shift.
        Set cur_lo_shifted to cur_lo_shifted bitwise and 9223372036854775807
        Set cur_lo to cur_lo_shifted bitwise or new_lo_high_part
        Let cur_hi_shifted be cur_hi shifted right by 1
        Set cur_hi_shifted to cur_hi_shifted bitwise and 9223372036854775807
        Set cur_hi to cur_hi_shifted
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Set cur_lo to cur_lo bitwise or sticky
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_hi_ptr, 0, cur_hi
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_lo_ptr, 0, cur_lo
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "f128_shift_left128" takes hi as Integer, lo as Integer, count as Integer, out_hi_ptr as Integer, out_lo_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Shift a 128-bit value left by `count`, dropping bits that fall off
    the top.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Bitwise loop. Cap count to 128.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Bounded loop with one OR per iteration.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    If count is less than or equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_hi_ptr, 0, hi
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_lo_ptr, 0, lo
        Return 0
    End If
    Let n be count
    If n is greater than 128:
        Set n to 128
    End If
    Let cur_hi be hi
    Let cur_lo be lo
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than n:
        Let lo_topbit be cur_lo shifted right by 63
        Set lo_topbit to lo_topbit bitwise and 1
        Set cur_hi to cur_hi shifted left by 1
        Set cur_hi to cur_hi bitwise or lo_topbit
        Set cur_lo to cur_lo shifted left by 1
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_hi_ptr, 0, cur_hi
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_lo_ptr, 0, cur_lo
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Unary
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "f128_neg" takes arena as Integer, p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Negate by flipping the sign bit, in a fresh buffer.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Copy + XOR sign bit.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    16-byte copy + one ALU.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Buffer owned by arena.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let q be proc f128_alloc with arena
    If q is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let hi be proc f128_load_high with p
    Let lo be proc f128_load_low with p
    Set hi to hi bitwise xor F128_HIGH_SIGN_MASK
    proc f128_store_high with q, hi
    proc f128_store_low with q, lo
    Return q
End Process

Process called "f128_abs" takes arena as Integer, p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Absolute value clears the sign bit, in a fresh buffer.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Copy + clear sign bit.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    16-byte copy + one ALU.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Buffer owned by arena.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let q be proc f128_alloc with arena
    If q is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let hi be proc f128_load_high with p
    Let lo be proc f128_load_low with p
    Set hi to hi bitwise and 9223372036854775807
    proc f128_store_high with q, hi
    proc f128_store_low with q, lo
    Return q
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Comparison
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "f128_compare" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Three-way ordered comparison. Returns -1, 0, 1 for less/equal/greater
    and 2 for unordered (NaN involved). Per IEEE 754 § 5.11.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    NaN dispatch, then sign-aware magnitude comparison.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    A few branches; magnitude compare is one 128-bit unsigned compare.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let a_nan be proc f128_is_nan with a
    If a_nan is equal to 1:
        Return 2
    End If
    Let b_nan be proc f128_is_nan with b
    If b_nan is equal to 1:
        Return 2
    End If

    Let a_zero be proc f128_is_zero with a
    Let b_zero be proc f128_is_zero with b
    If a_zero is equal to 1:
        If b_zero is equal to 1:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    Let sign_a be proc f128_get_sign with a
    Let sign_b be proc f128_get_sign with b

    Let a_hi be proc f128_load_high with a
    Let a_lo be proc f128_load_low with a
    Let b_hi be proc f128_load_high with b
    Let b_lo be proc f128_load_low with b
    Let mag_a_hi be a_hi bitwise and 9223372036854775807
    Let mag_b_hi be b_hi bitwise and 9223372036854775807

    If sign_a is equal to sign_b:
        Let cmp_mag be proc f128_compare128 with mag_a_hi, a_lo, mag_b_hi, b_lo
        If sign_a is equal to 0:
            Return cmp_mag
        End If
        Note: both negative: reverse
        If cmp_mag is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        If cmp_mag is equal to -1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return -1
    End If
    If sign_a is equal to 1:
        Return -1
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "f128_eq" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    IEEE 754 ==: false if NaN involved.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Delegate to f128_compare.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Same as compare.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let c be proc f128_compare with a, b
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "f128_ne" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    IEEE 754 !=.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Inverse of eq except for NaN where it's true (compare returns 2).
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Same as compare.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let c be proc f128_compare with a, b
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "f128_lt" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    IEEE 754 <.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    compare == -1.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Same as compare.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let c be proc f128_compare with a, b
    If c is equal to -1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "f128_le" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    IEEE 754 <=.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    compare in {-1, 0}.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Same as compare.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let c be proc f128_compare with a, b
    If c is equal to -1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "f128_gt" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    IEEE 754 >.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    compare == 1.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Same as compare.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let c be proc f128_compare with a, b
    If c is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "f128_ge" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    IEEE 754 >=.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    compare in {0, 1}.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Same as compare.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let c be proc f128_compare with a, b
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    If c is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Addition / subtraction
Note: ============================================================================
Note: We implement these by extracting fields, adding the hidden bit, aligning
Note: exponents (right-shift smaller with sticky), and packing back with
Note: rounding.
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "f128_finalize" takes arena as Integer, sign as Integer, unbiased_exp as Integer, mant_hi as Integer, mant_lo as Integer, guard as Integer, round_bit as Integer, sticky as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Final rounding + packing for a normalized (or normalize-pending) 113-bit
    mantissa (hidden bit at position 112) extended with three rounding bits.
    Handles overflow to Inf, underflow to subnormal/zero, and applies the
    active rounding mode.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Steps:
      1. If the mantissa is zero, return signed zero.
      2. Normalize: left-shift until bit 112 of the (mant_hi, mant_lo) pair
         is set. Adjust the exponent accordingly. If bit > 112, right-shift
         (with sticky accumulation) until bit 112 is set.
      3. Apply bias.
      4. If biased < 1, denormalize: right-shift mantissa with sticky.
      5. Use existing guard/round/sticky to decide on the rounding
         increment using the current mode.
      6. If increment causes the mantissa to overflow position 112, shift
         right by 1 and bump the exponent.
      7. Overflow / underflow / normal pack.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    A few bounded loops; otherwise constant time.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Buffer owned by arena.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let result be proc f128_alloc with arena
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let m_hi be mant_hi
    Let m_lo be mant_lo
    Let exp be unbiased_exp
    Let g be guard
    Let r be round_bit
    Let s be sticky

    Note: --- Zero mantissa check ---
    If m_hi is equal to 0:
        If m_lo is equal to 0:
            If g is equal to 0:
                If r is equal to 0:
                    If s is equal to 0:
                        If sign is equal to 1:
                            proc f128_store_high with result, F128_HIGH_SIGN_MASK
                        End If
                        Return result
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: --- Right-normalize if bit > 112 ---
    Note: bit 112 of (m_hi:m_lo) lies at bit 48 of m_hi.
    Let bit112_mask be 281474976710656
    Note: Test if any bits above 112: bits 49..63 of m_hi
    Let upper_mask be -281474976710656
    Set upper_mask to upper_mask bitwise and 9223372036854775807
    Note: equivalent: bits 49..62 + bit 63 if positive; we just use a raw
    Note: bound on m_hi.
    While m_hi is greater than 562949953421311:
        Note: 562949953421311 = (2^49 - 1); shift right while above this
        Let lo_bit be m_lo bitwise and 1
        Set s to s bitwise or r
        Set r to g
        Set g to lo_bit
        Note: shift right by 1 across the 128-bit pair, logical
        Let hi_lowbit be m_hi bitwise and 1
        Let new_lo_high_part be hi_lowbit shifted left by 63
        Let m_lo_shifted be m_lo shifted right by 1
        Set m_lo_shifted to m_lo_shifted bitwise and 9223372036854775807
        Set m_lo to m_lo_shifted bitwise or new_lo_high_part
        Let m_hi_shifted be m_hi shifted right by 1
        Set m_hi_shifted to m_hi_shifted bitwise and 9223372036854775807
        Set m_hi to m_hi_shifted
        Set exp to exp plus 1
    End While

    Note: --- Left-normalize if bit 112 not set ---
    Let top_bit be m_hi bitwise and bit112_mask
    While top_bit is equal to 0:
        If m_hi is equal to 0:
            If m_lo is equal to 0:
                Note: All bits gone. If sticky etc are zero, signed zero.
                If g is equal to 0:
                    If r is equal to 0:
                        If s is equal to 0:
                            If sign is equal to 1:
                                proc f128_store_high with result, F128_HIGH_SIGN_MASK
                            End If
                            Return result
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
                Note: tiny: drop into denormal handling below by breaking
                Set top_bit to bit112_mask
            End If
        End If
        If top_bit is equal to 0:
            Note: shift left 1; pull guard/round/sticky in
            Let lo_topbit be m_lo shifted right by 63
            Set lo_topbit to lo_topbit bitwise and 1
            Set m_hi to m_hi shifted left by 1
            Set m_hi to m_hi bitwise or lo_topbit
            Set m_lo to m_lo shifted left by 1
            Set m_lo to m_lo bitwise or g
            Set g to r
            Set r to s
            Set s to 0
            Set exp to exp minus 1
            Set top_bit to m_hi bitwise and bit112_mask
        End If
    End While

    Note: --- Bias ---
    Let biased be exp plus F128_BIAS

    Note: --- Denormalize if biased < 1 ---
    If biased is less than 1:
        Let shift_n be 1 minus biased
        Set biased to 0
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than shift_n:
            Let lo_b be m_lo bitwise and 1
            Set s to s bitwise or r
            Set r to g
            Set g to lo_b
            Let hi_low be m_hi bitwise and 1
            Let new_lo_h be hi_low shifted left by 63
            Let m_lo_sh be m_lo shifted right by 1
            Set m_lo_sh to m_lo_sh bitwise and 9223372036854775807
            Set m_lo to m_lo_sh bitwise or new_lo_h
            Let m_hi_sh be m_hi shifted right by 1
            Set m_hi_sh to m_hi_sh bitwise and 9223372036854775807
            Set m_hi to m_hi_sh
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Note: --- Round ---
    Let inexact_flag be g bitwise or r
    Set inexact_flag to inexact_flag bitwise or s

    Let increment be 0
    If F128_ROUNDING_MODE is equal to ROUND_NEAREST_EVEN:
        If g is equal to 1:
            If r is equal to 1:
                Set increment to 1
            Otherwise:
                If s is equal to 1:
                    Set increment to 1
                Otherwise:
                    Note: tie - round to even
                    Let lsb be m_lo bitwise and 1
                    If lsb is equal to 1:
                        Set increment to 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If
    If F128_ROUNDING_MODE is equal to ROUND_TOWARD_ZERO:
        Set increment to 0
    End If
    If F128_ROUNDING_MODE is equal to ROUND_TOWARD_POSITIVE:
        If sign is equal to 0:
            If inexact_flag is not equal to 0:
                Set increment to 1
            End If
        End If
    End If
    If F128_ROUNDING_MODE is equal to ROUND_TOWARD_NEGATIVE:
        If sign is equal to 1:
            If inexact_flag is not equal to 0:
                Set increment to 1
            End If
        End If
    End If

    If increment is equal to 1:
        Note: increment (m_hi, m_lo) by 1
        Let new_lo_inc be m_lo plus 1
        Let carry_inc be 0
        Note: unsigned overflow if m_lo was -1 (all-ones) and increment carried
        If m_lo is equal to -1:
            Set carry_inc to 1
        End If
        Set m_lo to new_lo_inc
        If carry_inc is equal to 1:
            Set m_hi to m_hi plus 1
        End If

        Note: Mantissa overflow: if bit 113 became set, shift right by 1 and bump exp
        Let bit113_mask be 562949953421312
        If (m_hi bitwise and bit113_mask) is not equal to 0:
            Let lo_b2 be m_lo bitwise and 1
            Set s to s bitwise or lo_b2
            Let hi_low2 be m_hi bitwise and 1
            Let new_lo_h2 be hi_low2 shifted left by 63
            Let m_lo_sh2 be m_lo shifted right by 1
            Set m_lo_sh2 to m_lo_sh2 bitwise and 9223372036854775807
            Set m_lo to m_lo_sh2 bitwise or new_lo_h2
            Let m_hi_sh2 be m_hi shifted right by 1
            Set m_hi_sh2 to m_hi_sh2 bitwise and 9223372036854775807
            Set m_hi to m_hi_sh2
            Set biased to biased plus 1
        End If
    End If

    Note: --- Subnormal-to-normal promotion ---
    If biased is equal to 0:
        If (m_hi bitwise and bit112_mask) is not equal to 0:
            Set biased to 1
        End If
    End If

    Note: --- Overflow ---
    If biased is greater than or equal to F128_EXP_MAX:
        Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_OVERFLOW
        Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INEXACT
        Note: Round toward zero / toward away from infinity yields largest finite
        If F128_ROUNDING_MODE is equal to ROUND_TOWARD_ZERO:
            proc f128_set_fields with result, sign, 32766, F128_HIGH_MANT_MASK, -1
            Return result
        End If
        If F128_ROUNDING_MODE is equal to ROUND_TOWARD_POSITIVE:
            If sign is equal to 1:
                proc f128_set_fields with result, sign, 32766, F128_HIGH_MANT_MASK, -1
                Return result
            End If
        End If
        If F128_ROUNDING_MODE is equal to ROUND_TOWARD_NEGATIVE:
            If sign is equal to 0:
                proc f128_set_fields with result, sign, 32766, F128_HIGH_MANT_MASK, -1
                Return result
            End If
        End If
        Let hi_inf be F128_EXP_MAX shifted left by 48
        If sign is equal to 1:
            Set hi_inf to hi_inf bitwise or F128_HIGH_SIGN_MASK
        End If
        proc f128_store_high with result, hi_inf
        Return result
    End If

    Note: --- Underflow to zero ---
    If biased is equal to 0:
        If m_hi is equal to 0:
            If m_lo is equal to 0:
                If inexact_flag is not equal to 0:
                    Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_UNDERFLOW
                    Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INEXACT
                End If
                If sign is equal to 1:
                    proc f128_store_high with result, F128_HIGH_SIGN_MASK
                End If
                Return result
            End If
        End If
        Note: subnormal result
        If inexact_flag is not equal to 0:
            Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_UNDERFLOW
            Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INEXACT
        End If
        Let m_hi_field be m_hi bitwise and F128_HIGH_MANT_MASK
        proc f128_set_fields with result, sign, 0, m_hi_field, m_lo
        Return result
    End If

    If inexact_flag is not equal to 0:
        Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INEXACT
    End If

    Note: --- Normal result: drop hidden bit ---
    Let m_hi_normal be m_hi bitwise and F128_HIGH_MANT_MASK
    proc f128_set_fields with result, sign, biased, m_hi_normal, m_lo
    Return result
End Process

Process called "f128_propagate_nan" takes arena as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Yield a quiet NaN. If any input is signaling, set INVALID flag.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Inspect both operands.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    A few branches.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Module-global flag mutation.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let a_snan be proc f128_is_signaling_nan with a
    Let b_snan be proc f128_is_signaling_nan with b
    If a_snan is equal to 1:
        Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INVALID
    End If
    If b_snan is equal to 1:
        Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INVALID
    End If
    Let a_nan be proc f128_is_nan with a
    If a_nan is equal to 1:
        Let q be proc f128_alloc with arena
        Let hi be proc f128_load_high with a
        Let lo be proc f128_load_low with a
        Note: Quiet the NaN by setting the mantissa MSB (bit 47 of high word).
        Let quiet_mask be 140737488355328
        Set hi to hi bitwise or quiet_mask
        proc f128_store_high with q, hi
        proc f128_store_low with q, lo
        Return q
    End If
    Let q2 be proc f128_alloc with arena
    Let hi2 be proc f128_load_high with b
    Let lo2 be proc f128_load_low with b
    Let quiet_mask_b be 140737488355328
    Set hi2 to hi2 bitwise or quiet_mask_b
    proc f128_store_high with q2, hi2
    proc f128_store_low with q2, lo2
    Return q2
End Process

Process called "f128_add" takes arena as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    IEEE 754 binary128 addition with correct rounding and special-value
    semantics per IEEE 754 § 6.1 and § 5.4.1.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    1. NaN propagation; Inf+Inf agreement check.
    2. Zero handling.
    3. Extract sign/exp/(mant_hi 48-bit, mant_lo 64-bit). Add hidden bit
       at bit 48 of mant_hi (yielding a 113-bit value with bit 112 set).
    4. Align: right-shift the smaller-exponent mantissa, accumulating
       sticky.
    5. Same-sign add or different-sign subtract.
    6. Hand to f128_finalize for normalization, rounding, packing.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    A few branches + a bounded shift loop.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Mutates exception flags.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let a_nan be proc f128_is_nan with a
    Let b_nan be proc f128_is_nan with b
    If a_nan is equal to 1:
        Return proc f128_propagate_nan with arena, a, b
    End If
    If b_nan is equal to 1:
        Return proc f128_propagate_nan with arena, a, b
    End If

    Let sign_a be proc f128_get_sign with a
    Let sign_b be proc f128_get_sign with b
    Let a_inf be proc f128_is_inf with a
    Let b_inf be proc f128_is_inf with b
    If a_inf is equal to 1:
        If b_inf is equal to 1:
            If sign_a is equal to sign_b:
                Return proc f128_make_inf with arena, sign_a
            End If
            Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INVALID
            Return proc f128_make_qnan with arena
        End If
        Note: a is Inf, b finite: return a
        Let r1 be proc f128_alloc with arena
        proc f128_store_high with r1, proc f128_load_high with a
        proc f128_store_low with r1, proc f128_load_low with a
        Return r1
    End If
    If b_inf is equal to 1:
        Let r2 be proc f128_alloc with arena
        proc f128_store_high with r2, proc f128_load_high with b
        proc f128_store_low with r2, proc f128_load_low with b
        Return r2
    End If

    Let a_zero be proc f128_is_zero with a
    Let b_zero be proc f128_is_zero with b
    If a_zero is equal to 1:
        If b_zero is equal to 1:
            If sign_a is equal to sign_b:
                Return proc f128_make_zero with arena, sign_a
            End If
            If F128_ROUNDING_MODE is equal to ROUND_TOWARD_NEGATIVE:
                Return proc f128_make_zero with arena, 1
            End If
            Return proc f128_make_zero with arena, 0
        End If
        Let rb be proc f128_alloc with arena
        proc f128_store_high with rb, proc f128_load_high with b
        proc f128_store_low with rb, proc f128_load_low with b
        Return rb
    End If
    If b_zero is equal to 1:
        Let ra be proc f128_alloc with arena
        proc f128_store_high with ra, proc f128_load_high with a
        proc f128_store_low with ra, proc f128_load_low with a
        Return ra
    End If

    Let exp_a be proc f128_get_exponent with a
    Let exp_b be proc f128_get_exponent with b
    Let mh_a be proc f128_get_mantissa_high with a
    Let ml_a be proc f128_get_mantissa_low with a
    Let mh_b be proc f128_get_mantissa_high with b
    Let ml_b be proc f128_get_mantissa_low with b

    Let true_exp_a be exp_a
    Let true_exp_b be exp_b
    If exp_a is equal to 0:
        Set true_exp_a to 1
    Otherwise:
        Set mh_a to mh_a bitwise or F128_HIDDEN_BIT_HIGH
    End If
    If exp_b is equal to 0:
        Set true_exp_b to 1
    Otherwise:
        Set mh_b to mh_b bitwise or F128_HIDDEN_BIT_HIGH
    End If

    Let aligned_exp be true_exp_a
    Let g be 0
    Let r be 0
    Let s be 0

    If true_exp_a is less than true_exp_b:
        Let diff be true_exp_b minus true_exp_a
        Note: Cap shift to keep loop bounded; 130 is enough since the
        Note: mantissa has 113 bits + 3 GRS slots.
        If diff is greater than 130:
            Set diff to 130
        End If
        Note: We do a 128-bit right shift with sticky on the (mh_a, ml_a) pair.
        Note: Save the last 3 shifted bits into g/r/s.
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than diff:
            Let lost_bit be ml_a bitwise and 1
            Set s to s bitwise or r
            Set r to g
            Set g to lost_bit
            Let hi_low be mh_a bitwise and 1
            Let new_lo_h be hi_low shifted left by 63
            Let ml_a_sh be ml_a shifted right by 1
            Set ml_a_sh to ml_a_sh bitwise and 9223372036854775807
            Set ml_a to ml_a_sh bitwise or new_lo_h
            Let mh_a_sh be mh_a shifted right by 1
            Set mh_a_sh to mh_a_sh bitwise and 9223372036854775807
            Set mh_a to mh_a_sh
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Set aligned_exp to true_exp_b
    End If
    If true_exp_b is less than true_exp_a:
        Let diff_b be true_exp_a minus true_exp_b
        If diff_b is greater than 130:
            Set diff_b to 130
        End If
        Let j be 0
        While j is less than diff_b:
            Let lost_bit_b be ml_b bitwise and 1
            Set s to s bitwise or r
            Set r to g
            Set g to lost_bit_b
            Let hi_low_b be mh_b bitwise and 1
            Let new_lo_h_b be hi_low_b shifted left by 63
            Let ml_b_sh be ml_b shifted right by 1
            Set ml_b_sh to ml_b_sh bitwise and 9223372036854775807
            Set ml_b to ml_b_sh bitwise or new_lo_h_b
            Let mh_b_sh be mh_b shifted right by 1
            Set mh_b_sh to mh_b_sh bitwise and 9223372036854775807
            Set mh_b to mh_b_sh
            Set j to j plus 1
        End While
        Set aligned_exp to true_exp_a
    End If

    Let result_sign be sign_a
    Let res_hi be 0
    Let res_lo be 0

    If sign_a is equal to sign_b:
        Let hi_buf be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 8
        Let lo_buf be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 8
        proc f128_add128 with mh_a, ml_a, mh_b, ml_b, hi_buf, lo_buf
        Set res_hi to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with hi_buf, 0
        Set res_lo to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lo_buf, 0
        Set result_sign to sign_a
    Otherwise:
        Let cmp be proc f128_compare128 with mh_a, ml_a, mh_b, ml_b
        Let hi_buf2 be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 8
        Let lo_buf2 be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 8
        If cmp is greater than or equal to 0:
            proc f128_sub128 with mh_a, ml_a, mh_b, ml_b, hi_buf2, lo_buf2
            Set result_sign to sign_a
        Otherwise:
            proc f128_sub128 with mh_b, ml_b, mh_a, ml_a, hi_buf2, lo_buf2
            Set result_sign to sign_b
        End If
        Set res_hi to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with hi_buf2, 0
        Set res_lo to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lo_buf2, 0
    End If

    If res_hi is equal to 0:
        If res_lo is equal to 0:
            If g is equal to 0:
                If r is equal to 0:
                    If s is equal to 0:
                        If F128_ROUNDING_MODE is equal to ROUND_TOWARD_NEGATIVE:
                            Return proc f128_make_zero with arena, 1
                        End If
                        Return proc f128_make_zero with arena, 0
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Let unbiased be aligned_exp minus F128_BIAS
    Return proc f128_finalize with arena, result_sign, unbiased, res_hi, res_lo, g, r, s
End Process

Process called "f128_sub" takes arena as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    a - b = a + (-b).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Negate then add.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Costs one extra allocate.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Inherits f128_add behavior.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let neg_b be proc f128_neg with arena, b
    Return proc f128_add with arena, a, neg_b
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Multiplication
Note: ============================================================================
Note: For binary128 we need a 112*112 -> 224-bit (effectively 226 with hidden
Note: bits) product. We split each mantissa into a high 64-bit limb (top of
Note: mantissa) and a low 64-bit limb, multiply the four cross-products,
Note: and assemble. Each cross-product is a 64*64->128 expansion, which we
Note: implement via mul64x64_128 (32-bit halving classical algorithm).
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "f128_mul64x64_to_128" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, hi_ptr as Integer, lo_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Multiply two unsigned 64-bit values, returning the 128-bit product
    in (hi, lo). Uses 32-bit limb decomposition: a = a_hi*2^32 + a_lo,
    b = b_hi*2^32 + b_lo; product is
        a_lo*b_lo + 2^32*(a_lo*b_hi + a_hi*b_lo) + 2^64*a_hi*b_hi.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Each partial fits in 64 bits because (2^32-1)^2 < 2^64. Assemble
    with careful carry propagation.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Four 32x32 multiplications and a few additions. On x86-64 the obvious
    lowering is a single mulq; we provide the portable form here.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let mask32 be 4294967295
    Let a_lo be a bitwise and mask32
    Let a_hi be (a shifted right by 32) bitwise and mask32
    Let b_lo be b bitwise and mask32
    Let b_hi be (b shifted right by 32) bitwise and mask32

    Let p_ll be a_lo multiplied by b_lo
    Let p_lh be a_lo multiplied by b_hi
    Let p_hl be a_hi multiplied by b_lo
    Let p_hh be a_hi multiplied by b_hi

    Let lo_low be p_ll bitwise and mask32
    Let lo_high_p be p_ll shifted right by 32
    Set lo_high_p to lo_high_p bitwise and mask32

    Let mid be lo_high_p plus (p_lh bitwise and mask32)
    Set mid to mid plus (p_hl bitwise and mask32)
    Let mid_low be mid bitwise and mask32
    Let mid_carry be mid shifted right by 32

    Let result_lo be (mid_low shifted left by 32) bitwise or lo_low

    Let upper be p_hh plus (p_lh shifted right by 32)
    Set upper to upper plus (p_hl shifted right by 32)
    Set upper to upper plus mid_carry

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with hi_ptr, 0, upper
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with lo_ptr, 0, result_lo
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "f128_mul" takes arena as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    IEEE 754 binary128 multiplication with correct rounding.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    1. NaN/Inf/zero dispatch.
    2. Normalize each operand, add hidden bit, treat 113-bit mantissa.
    3. Multiply 113x113 -> ~226-bit value carried as four 64-bit limbs.
       We approximate using two 128-bit splits and the f128_mul64x64_to_128
       primitive: split mantissas into top64+bottom49 (mh has 49 used bits
       for normal numbers, since hidden bit at position 48 and 48 fraction
       bits), bottom = ml (64 bits). Use Karatsuba-style assembly.
    4. Shift the product so the leading set bit aligns at position 112,
       OR shifted-out bits into the sticky bit, and hand to f128_finalize.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Four 64x64 multiplications, a few shifts/adds.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Mutates exception flags.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let a_nan be proc f128_is_nan with a
    Let b_nan be proc f128_is_nan with b
    If a_nan is equal to 1:
        Return proc f128_propagate_nan with arena, a, b
    End If
    If b_nan is equal to 1:
        Return proc f128_propagate_nan with arena, a, b
    End If

    Let sign_a be proc f128_get_sign with a
    Let sign_b be proc f128_get_sign with b
    Let result_sign be sign_a bitwise xor sign_b

    Let a_inf be proc f128_is_inf with a
    Let b_inf be proc f128_is_inf with b
    Let a_zero be proc f128_is_zero with a
    Let b_zero be proc f128_is_zero with b
    If a_inf is equal to 1:
        If b_zero is equal to 1:
            Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INVALID
            Return proc f128_make_qnan with arena
        End If
        Return proc f128_make_inf with arena, result_sign
    End If
    If b_inf is equal to 1:
        If a_zero is equal to 1:
            Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INVALID
            Return proc f128_make_qnan with arena
        End If
        Return proc f128_make_inf with arena, result_sign
    End If
    If a_zero is equal to 1:
        Return proc f128_make_zero with arena, result_sign
    End If
    If b_zero is equal to 1:
        Return proc f128_make_zero with arena, result_sign
    End If

    Let exp_a be proc f128_get_exponent with a
    Let exp_b be proc f128_get_exponent with b
    Let mh_a be proc f128_get_mantissa_high with a
    Let ml_a be proc f128_get_mantissa_low with a
    Let mh_b be proc f128_get_mantissa_high with b
    Let ml_b be proc f128_get_mantissa_low with b

    Let true_exp_a be exp_a
    Let true_exp_b be exp_b
    If exp_a is equal to 0:
        Set true_exp_a to 1
        Note: Normalize subnormal: shift left until hidden bit set.
        While (mh_a bitwise and F128_HIDDEN_BIT_HIGH) is equal to 0:
            Let ml_a_top be ml_a shifted right by 63
            Set ml_a_top to ml_a_top bitwise and 1
            Set mh_a to mh_a shifted left by 1
            Set mh_a to mh_a bitwise or ml_a_top
            Set ml_a to ml_a shifted left by 1
            Set true_exp_a to true_exp_a minus 1
        End While
    Otherwise:
        Set mh_a to mh_a bitwise or F128_HIDDEN_BIT_HIGH
    End If
    If exp_b is equal to 0:
        Set true_exp_b to 1
        While (mh_b bitwise and F128_HIDDEN_BIT_HIGH) is equal to 0:
            Let ml_b_top be ml_b shifted right by 63
            Set ml_b_top to ml_b_top bitwise and 1
            Set mh_b to mh_b shifted left by 1
            Set mh_b to mh_b bitwise or ml_b_top
            Set ml_b to ml_b shifted left by 1
            Set true_exp_b to true_exp_b minus 1
        End While
    Otherwise:
        Set mh_b to mh_b bitwise or F128_HIDDEN_BIT_HIGH
    End If

    Note: Build a 128-bit value from (mh_a:ml_a) holding 113 bits with the
    Note: hidden bit at position 48 of mh_a (= bit 112 overall). Same for b.
    Note: Multiply as 128x128 -> 256-bit. We carry the 256-bit result as
    Note: four 64-bit limbs: p3 (top), p2, p1, p0 (bottom).

    Note: Compute four cross products: a_lo*b_lo, a_lo*b_hi, a_hi*b_lo, a_hi*b_hi
    Note: where a_hi=mh_a, a_lo=ml_a, b_hi=mh_b, b_lo=ml_b. Each is 64x64 -> 128.
    Let buf_hi_ll be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 8
    Let buf_lo_ll be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 8
    proc f128_mul64x64_to_128 with ml_a, ml_b, buf_hi_ll, buf_lo_ll
    Let p_ll_hi be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with buf_hi_ll, 0
    Let p_ll_lo be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with buf_lo_ll, 0

    Let buf_hi_lh be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 8
    Let buf_lo_lh be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 8
    proc f128_mul64x64_to_128 with ml_a, mh_b, buf_hi_lh, buf_lo_lh
    Let p_lh_hi be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with buf_hi_lh, 0
    Let p_lh_lo be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with buf_lo_lh, 0

    Let buf_hi_hl be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 8
    Let buf_lo_hl be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 8
    proc f128_mul64x64_to_128 with mh_a, ml_b, buf_hi_hl, buf_lo_hl
    Let p_hl_hi be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with buf_hi_hl, 0
    Let p_hl_lo be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with buf_lo_hl, 0

    Let buf_hi_hh be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 8
    Let buf_lo_hh be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 8
    proc f128_mul64x64_to_128 with mh_a, mh_b, buf_hi_hh, buf_lo_hh
    Let p_hh_hi be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with buf_hi_hh, 0
    Let p_hh_lo be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with buf_lo_hh, 0

    Note: Assemble 256-bit result. Position assignments (in 64-bit limbs):
    Note:   p_ll occupies limbs (0, 1)        - bits 0..127
    Note:   p_lh occupies limbs (1, 2)        - bits 64..191
    Note:   p_hl occupies limbs (1, 2)        - bits 64..191
    Note:   p_hh occupies limbs (2, 3)        - bits 128..255
    Let limb0 be p_ll_lo
    Let limb1_init be p_ll_hi
    Let limb2_init be 0
    Let limb3_init be 0

    Note: Add p_lh into (limb1, limb2)
    Let bufh1 be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 8
    Let bufl1 be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 8
    proc f128_add128 with limb2_init, limb1_init, p_lh_hi, p_lh_lo, bufh1, bufl1
    Let limb2_a be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bufh1, 0
    Let limb1_a be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bufl1, 0
    Note: Detect carry into limb3 if limb2 wrapped.
    Let carry_into3_a be 0
    Let xor_a_hi be limb2_init bitwise xor limb2_a
    Let and_check_a be xor_a_hi bitwise and p_lh_hi
    Note: A simpler detection: if (limb2_a, limb1_a) is unsigned-less than (p_lh_hi, p_lh_lo) - skip; we instead reuse our add128 helper symmetrically below.

    Note: Add p_hl into (limb1_a, limb2_a)
    Let bufh2 be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 8
    Let bufl2 be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 8
    proc f128_add128 with limb2_a, limb1_a, p_hl_hi, p_hl_lo, bufh2, bufl2
    Let limb2_b be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bufh2, 0
    Let limb1_b be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bufl2, 0

    Note: Add p_hh into (limb2_b, limb3_init)
    Let bufh3 be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 8
    Let bufl3 be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 8
    proc f128_add128 with limb3_init, limb2_b, p_hh_hi, p_hh_lo, bufh3, bufl3
    Let limb3 be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bufh3, 0
    Let limb2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bufl3, 0
    Let limb1 be limb1_b

    Note: Now the 256-bit product (limb3, limb2, limb1, limb0) represents
    Note: the 226-bit integer product of the two 113-bit mantissas, with
    Note: the leading bit somewhere in limb2 / limb3.

    Note: The expected leading bit position: if both inputs had bit 112 set
    Note: (which they do because they're normalized), the product has bit
    Note: 224 set, OR bit 225 set if the multiplication produced a carry
    Note: into the next binade. We want the result mantissa to have its
    Note: hidden bit at position 112 (= bit 48 of limb1 in our packed
    Note: layout if we shift right by 112 bits).

    Note: Shift the 256-bit product right by 112 bits, accumulating
    Note: shifted-out 1-bits into the sticky bit. After the shift the
    Note: leading bit should be at position 112 (or 113 -> caller's
    Note: f128_finalize will right-normalize).

    Let sticky_acc be 0
    Let p3 be limb3
    Let p2 be limb2
    Let p1 be limb1
    Let p0 be limb0
    Let k be 0
    While k is less than 112:
        Let lost be p0 bitwise and 1
        Set sticky_acc to sticky_acc bitwise or lost
        Note: shift 256-bit value right by 1 logically
        Let p1_low be p1 bitwise and 1
        Let p2_low be p2 bitwise and 1
        Let p3_low be p3 bitwise and 1
        Let p0_sh be p0 shifted right by 1
        Set p0_sh to p0_sh bitwise and 9223372036854775807
        Set p0 to p0_sh bitwise or (p1_low shifted left by 63)
        Let p1_sh be p1 shifted right by 1
        Set p1_sh to p1_sh bitwise and 9223372036854775807
        Set p1 to p1_sh bitwise or (p2_low shifted left by 63)
        Let p2_sh be p2 shifted right by 1
        Set p2_sh to p2_sh bitwise and 9223372036854775807
        Set p2 to p2_sh bitwise or (p3_low shifted left by 63)
        Let p3_sh be p3 shifted right by 1
        Set p3_sh to p3_sh bitwise and 9223372036854775807
        Set p3 to p3_sh
        Set k to k plus 1
    End While

    Note: At this point (p1, p0) holds the trailing 128 bits and (p3, p2)
    Note: hold the leading 128 bits. The leading set bit is in (p3, p2)
    Note: at position ~112 (bit 48 of p3 if no carry, bit 49 if carry).
    Note: Combine into the 128-bit mantissa pair (m_hi, m_lo) = (p3, p2)
    Note: discarding p1, p0 except for the GRS bits + sticky_acc.

    Let m_hi be p3
    Let m_lo be p2

    Note: Extract guard/round bits from p1's top two bits and sticky from
    Note: everything below.
    Let g be (p1 shifted right by 63) bitwise and 1
    Let r be (p1 shifted right by 62) bitwise and 1
    Note: All other bits of p1 + all of p0 + accumulated sticky_acc become sticky.
    Let s be sticky_acc
    Let p1_lower_mask be 4611686018427387903
    If (p1 bitwise and p1_lower_mask) is not equal to 0:
        Set s to 1
    End If
    If p0 is not equal to 0:
        Set s to 1
    End If

    Note:
    f128_finalize expects an UNBIASED exponent (it re-applies the bias
    inside). true_exp_a/_b are biased, so subtract the bias twice from
    their sum. Adding bias back at this stage doubles it and yields a
    result 2^16383 too large. Same shape as f32_mul fix under WAVE
    NUMERIC-FIX-SWEEP.
    :End Note
    Let unbiased be true_exp_a plus true_exp_b
    Set unbiased to unbiased minus F128_BIAS
    Set unbiased to unbiased minus F128_BIAS

    Return proc f128_finalize with arena, result_sign, unbiased, m_hi, m_lo, g, r, s
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Division (long division on 128-bit mantissas)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "f128_div" takes arena as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    IEEE 754 binary128 division with correct rounding.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    1. NaN/Inf/zero dispatch (including divide-by-zero flag).
    2. Normalize operands, attach hidden bit.
    3. Long-divide (mh_a:ml_a) << 113 by (mh_b:ml_b) to get a 113-bit
       quotient with hidden bit at position 112. Algorithm: bit-by-bit
       shift-subtract-restore.
    4. Sticky bit set if final remainder nonzero.
    5. Hand to f128_finalize.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    115-iteration loop (113 quotient bits + 2 guard/round bits); each
    iteration performs an unsigned 128-bit compare and a conditional
    128-bit subtract via f128_compare128 / f128_sub128. Faster algorithms
    (SRT, Newton) remain available as future replacements; this
    shift-subtract long division is the canonical reference.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Mutates exception flags.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let a_nan be proc f128_is_nan with a
    Let b_nan be proc f128_is_nan with b
    If a_nan is equal to 1:
        Return proc f128_propagate_nan with arena, a, b
    End If
    If b_nan is equal to 1:
        Return proc f128_propagate_nan with arena, a, b
    End If

    Let sign_a be proc f128_get_sign with a
    Let sign_b be proc f128_get_sign with b
    Let result_sign be sign_a bitwise xor sign_b

    Let a_inf be proc f128_is_inf with a
    Let b_inf be proc f128_is_inf with b
    Let a_zero be proc f128_is_zero with a
    Let b_zero be proc f128_is_zero with b

    If a_inf is equal to 1:
        If b_inf is equal to 1:
            Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INVALID
            Return proc f128_make_qnan with arena
        End If
        Return proc f128_make_inf with arena, result_sign
    End If
    If b_inf is equal to 1:
        Return proc f128_make_zero with arena, result_sign
    End If
    If b_zero is equal to 1:
        If a_zero is equal to 1:
            Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INVALID
            Return proc f128_make_qnan with arena
        End If
        Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_DIVIDE_BY_ZERO
        Return proc f128_make_inf with arena, result_sign
    End If
    If a_zero is equal to 1:
        Return proc f128_make_zero with arena, result_sign
    End If

    Let exp_a be proc f128_get_exponent with a
    Let exp_b be proc f128_get_exponent with b
    Let mh_a be proc f128_get_mantissa_high with a
    Let ml_a be proc f128_get_mantissa_low with a
    Let mh_b be proc f128_get_mantissa_high with b
    Let ml_b be proc f128_get_mantissa_low with b

    Let true_exp_a be exp_a
    Let true_exp_b be exp_b
    If exp_a is equal to 0:
        Set true_exp_a to 1
        While (mh_a bitwise and F128_HIDDEN_BIT_HIGH) is equal to 0:
            Let mtop be ml_a shifted right by 63
            Set mtop to mtop bitwise and 1
            Set mh_a to mh_a shifted left by 1
            Set mh_a to mh_a bitwise or mtop
            Set ml_a to ml_a shifted left by 1
            Set true_exp_a to true_exp_a minus 1
        End While
    Otherwise:
        Set mh_a to mh_a bitwise or F128_HIDDEN_BIT_HIGH
    End If
    If exp_b is equal to 0:
        Set true_exp_b to 1
        While (mh_b bitwise and F128_HIDDEN_BIT_HIGH) is equal to 0:
            Let mtop_b be ml_b shifted right by 63
            Set mtop_b to mtop_b bitwise and 1
            Set mh_b to mh_b shifted left by 1
            Set mh_b to mh_b bitwise or mtop_b
            Set ml_b to ml_b shifted left by 1
            Set true_exp_b to true_exp_b minus 1
        End While
    Otherwise:
        Set mh_b to mh_b bitwise or F128_HIDDEN_BIT_HIGH
    End If

    Note: Quotient computation: produce 115 quotient bits (113 result + 2 GRS).
    Note: Algorithm: shift-subtract long division.
    Let q_hi be 0
    Let q_lo be 0
    Let rem_hi be mh_a
    Let rem_lo be ml_a
    Let bits_needed be 115
    Let n be 0
    While n is less than bits_needed:
        Note: Shift rem left by 1 (across 128-bit pair).
        Let rem_lo_top be rem_lo shifted right by 63
        Set rem_lo_top to rem_lo_top bitwise and 1
        Set rem_hi to rem_hi shifted left by 1
        Set rem_hi to rem_hi bitwise or rem_lo_top
        Set rem_lo to rem_lo shifted left by 1
        Note: Shift q left by 1.
        Let q_lo_top be q_lo shifted right by 63
        Set q_lo_top to q_lo_top bitwise and 1
        Set q_hi to q_hi shifted left by 1
        Set q_hi to q_hi bitwise or q_lo_top
        Set q_lo to q_lo shifted left by 1
        Note: Compare rem >= divisor; if so, subtract and set q LSB.
        Let cmp be proc f128_compare128 with rem_hi, rem_lo, mh_b, ml_b
        If cmp is greater than or equal to 0:
            Let bufh be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 8
            Let bufl be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 8
            proc f128_sub128 with rem_hi, rem_lo, mh_b, ml_b, bufh, bufl
            Set rem_hi to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bufh, 0
            Set rem_lo to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bufl, 0
            Set q_lo to q_lo bitwise or 1
        End If
        Set n to n plus 1
    End While

    Note: q now has 115 bits. We want hidden bit at position 112 and 3 GRS
    Note: bits at positions 2..0. q layout: bits 114..0 across (q_hi, q_lo).
    Note: Extract guard = bit 2 of q_lo, round = bit 1, sticky = bit 0 OR
    Note: (rem nonzero).
    Let g be (q_lo shifted right by 2) bitwise and 1
    Let r be (q_lo shifted right by 1) bitwise and 1
    Let s be q_lo bitwise and 1
    If rem_hi is not equal to 0:
        Set s to 1
    End If
    If rem_lo is not equal to 0:
        Set s to 1
    End If

    Note: Shift q right by 3 to drop GRS bits.
    Let q_lo_sh be q_lo shifted right by 3
    Set q_lo_sh to q_lo_sh bitwise and 2305843009213693951
    Let q_hi_lowbits be q_hi bitwise and 7
    Let q_lo_final be q_lo_sh bitwise or (q_hi_lowbits shifted left by 61)
    Let q_hi_sh be q_hi shifted right by 3
    Set q_hi_sh to q_hi_sh bitwise and 2305843009213693951

    Let unbiased be true_exp_a minus true_exp_b
    Return proc f128_finalize with arena, result_sign, unbiased, q_hi_sh, q_lo_final, g, r, s
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Square root (Newton on the mantissa)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "f128_sqrt" takes arena as Integer, a as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Per IEEE 754 § 6.1: sqrt(-0) = -0, sqrt(+0) = +0, sqrt(+Inf) = +Inf,
    sqrt(-finite) = NaN, sqrt(NaN) = NaN.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Paper-and-pencil integer square root on the 113-bit mantissa shifted
    left by (113 - parity) so the radicand sits with its top bit at
    bit 225 of a 256-bit value held in four 64-bit limbs. The loop
    runs 115 times: 113 iterations produce the 113-bit root (with the
    hidden bit at position 112), then 2 additional iterations extract
    guard and round bits. Any nonzero residual after iteration 115
    forms the sticky bit. Round-to-nearest-ties-to-even is applied by
    f128_finalize from the guard, round, sticky bits.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    115 iterations; each iteration performs an unsigned 128-bit compare
    and (when the candidate fits) a 128-bit subtract, both already
    provided by f128_compare128 / f128_sub128.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Mutates exception flags.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let nan be proc f128_is_nan with a
    If nan is equal to 1:
        Return proc f128_propagate_nan with arena, a, a
    End If
    Let zero be proc f128_is_zero with a
    If zero is equal to 1:
        Let q be proc f128_alloc with arena
        proc f128_store_high with q, proc f128_load_high with a
        proc f128_store_low with q, proc f128_load_low with a
        Return q
    End If
    Let sign be proc f128_get_sign with a
    If sign is equal to 1:
        Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INVALID
        Return proc f128_make_qnan with arena
    End If
    Let inf be proc f128_is_inf with a
    If inf is equal to 1:
        Return proc f128_make_inf with arena, 0
    End If

    Let exp be proc f128_get_exponent with a
    Let mh be proc f128_get_mantissa_high with a
    Let ml be proc f128_get_mantissa_low with a

    Let true_exp be exp
    If exp is equal to 0:
        Set true_exp to 1
        While (mh bitwise and F128_HIDDEN_BIT_HIGH) is equal to 0:
            Let mtop be ml shifted right by 63
            Set mtop to mtop bitwise and 1
            Set mh to mh shifted left by 1
            Set mh to mh bitwise or mtop
            Set ml to ml shifted left by 1
            Set true_exp to true_exp minus 1
        End While
    Otherwise:
        Set mh to mh bitwise or F128_HIDDEN_BIT_HIGH
    End If

    Let unbiased be true_exp minus F128_BIAS
    Let parity be unbiased bitwise and 1
    If parity is not equal to 0:
        Note: shift mantissa left by 1 across (mh, ml)
        Let mlt be ml shifted right by 63
        Set mlt to mlt bitwise and 1
        Set mh to mh shifted left by 1
        Set mh to mh bitwise or mlt
        Set ml to ml shifted left by 1
        Set unbiased to unbiased minus 1
    End If
    Let result_exp be unbiased divided by 2

    Note: Build the radicand R = (mh:ml) << (113 - parity) so that its
    Note: top bit lies at position 225 of a 256-bit value held in four
    Note: 64-bit limbs (rad3:rad2:rad1:rad0). limb 0 spans bits 0..63,
    Note: limb 1 spans bits 64..127, limb 2 spans bits 128..191, limb 3
    Note: spans bits 192..255. The pre-parity-adjusted mantissa has its
    Note: hidden bit at bit 112; after the optional parity left-shift by
    Note: 1 the hidden bit is at bit 112 or 113 of (mh:ml). The total
    Note: shift = 225 - (112 + parity) = 113 - parity.
    Let bit_shift be 49 minus parity
    Note: Place (mh, ml) at limbs (2, 1); then left-shift the full 256-bit
    Note: value by bit_shift to position the top bit at bit 225.
    Let rad0 be 0
    Let rad1 be ml
    Let rad2 be mh
    Let rad3 be 0
    Let i_sh be 0
    While i_sh is less than bit_shift:
        Let carry0 be (rad0 shifted right by 63) bitwise and 1
        Let carry1 be (rad1 shifted right by 63) bitwise and 1
        Let carry2 be (rad2 shifted right by 63) bitwise and 1
        Set rad3 to ((rad3 shifted left by 1) bitwise or carry2)
        Set rad2 to ((rad2 shifted left by 1) bitwise or carry1)
        Set rad1 to ((rad1 shifted left by 1) bitwise or carry0)
        Set rad0 to rad0 shifted left by 1
        Set i_sh to i_sh plus 1
    End While

    Note: --- Paper-and-pencil isqrt on (rad3:rad2:rad1:rad0). Each
    Note: iteration extracts the next two-bit "digit" from the top of
    Note: the radicand, appends it to the running remainder, and tests
    Note: whether the trial root (2*root << 1 | 1) divides into the
    Note: remainder. 113 iterations produce the 113-bit root; 2 extra
    Note: iterations on appended zero bits extract guard and round
    Note: bits; any nonzero residual becomes the sticky bit. ---
    Let root_hi be 0
    Let root_lo be 0
    Let rem_hi be 0
    Let rem_lo be 0
    Let total_iters be 115
    Let iter be 0
    Note: pair_pos is the position of the LOW bit of the next 2-bit
    Note: window into N; it starts at 224 (so pair = bits 225..224) and
    Note: decrements by 2 each step. When pair_pos < 0 we feed in
    Note: zeros (the guard/round extension).
    Let pair_pos be 224
    While iter is less than total_iters:
        Note: Extract the next 2 bits of N from position (pair_pos+1, pair_pos).
        Let pair_bits be 0
        If pair_pos is greater than or equal to 0:
            Let limb_idx be pair_pos divided by 64
            Let bit_in_limb be pair_pos modulo by 64
            Let cur_limb be 0
            If limb_idx is equal to 0:
                Set cur_limb to rad0
            End If
            If limb_idx is equal to 1:
                Set cur_limb to rad1
            End If
            If limb_idx is equal to 2:
                Set cur_limb to rad2
            End If
            If limb_idx is equal to 3:
                Set cur_limb to rad3
            End If
            If bit_in_limb is equal to 63:
                Note: 2-bit window straddles the limb boundary.
                Let next_limb be 0
                If limb_idx is equal to 0:
                    Set next_limb to rad1
                End If
                If limb_idx is equal to 1:
                    Set next_limb to rad2
                End If
                If limb_idx is equal to 2:
                    Set next_limb to rad3
                End If
                Let lo_bit_val be (cur_limb shifted right by 63) bitwise and 1
                Let hi_bit_val be next_limb bitwise and 1
                Set pair_bits to ((hi_bit_val shifted left by 1) bitwise or lo_bit_val)
            Otherwise:
                Let shifted be cur_limb shifted right by bit_in_limb
                Set pair_bits to shifted bitwise and 3
            End If
        End If

        Note: rem = (rem << 2) | pair_bits  (128-bit shift)
        Let rem_lo_top2 be (rem_lo shifted right by 62) bitwise and 3
        Set rem_hi to ((rem_hi shifted left by 2) bitwise or rem_lo_top2)
        Set rem_lo to ((rem_lo shifted left by 2) bitwise or pair_bits)

        Note: test = (root << 1) | 1  (128-bit shift, low bit set)
        Let root_lo_top1 be (root_lo shifted right by 63) bitwise and 1
        Let test_hi be ((root_hi shifted left by 1) bitwise or root_lo_top1)
        Let test_lo be ((root_lo shifted left by 1) bitwise or 1)

        Note: Pre-compute the unconditional root-left-shift (bit-0 cleared).
        Let new_root_hi be ((root_hi shifted left by 1) bitwise or root_lo_top1)
        Let new_root_lo be (root_lo shifted left by 1)

        Note: Compare rem vs. test as unsigned 128-bit values.
        Let cmp_rt be proc f128_compare128 with rem_hi, rem_lo, test_hi, test_lo
        If cmp_rt is greater than or equal to 0:
            Note: Trial root fits: subtract test from rem and set root's LSB.
            Let sub_hi_ptr be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 8
            Let sub_lo_ptr be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, 8
            proc f128_sub128 with rem_hi, rem_lo, test_hi, test_lo, sub_hi_ptr, sub_lo_ptr
            Set rem_hi to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with sub_hi_ptr, 0
            Set rem_lo to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with sub_lo_ptr, 0
            Set new_root_lo to new_root_lo bitwise or 1
        End If
        Set root_hi to new_root_hi
        Set root_lo to new_root_lo

        Set pair_pos to pair_pos minus 2
        Set iter to iter plus 1
    End While

    Note: root now has 115 bits: top 113 are the integer square root
    Note: of N (with the hidden bit at position 114 of root), the
    Note: bottom 2 are guard (bit 1) and round (bit 0).
    Let g be (root_lo shifted right by 1) bitwise and 1
    Let r_bit be root_lo bitwise and 1
    Let sticky be 0
    If rem_hi is not equal to 0:
        Set sticky to 1
    End If
    If rem_lo is not equal to 0:
        Set sticky to 1
    End If

    Note: Strip the guard/round bits to recover the 113-bit mantissa
    Note: with hidden bit at position 112 of (m_hi:m_lo).
    Let m_lo_shifted be root_lo shifted right by 2
    Set m_lo_shifted to m_lo_shifted bitwise and 4611686018427387903
    Let m_hi_low2 be root_hi bitwise and 3
    Let m_lo_final be m_lo_shifted bitwise or (m_hi_low2 shifted left by 62)
    Let m_hi_shifted be root_hi shifted right by 2
    Set m_hi_shifted to m_hi_shifted bitwise and 4611686018427387903

    Return proc f128_finalize with arena, 0, result_exp, m_hi_shifted, m_lo_final, g, r_bit, sticky
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Fused multiply-add
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "f128_fma" takes arena as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer, c as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    a*b + c with a single rounding step per IEEE 754-2008 § 5.4.1.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Two-step path: compute a*b through the full 226-bit intermediate
    (already produced by f128_mul) then add c. The double-rounding in
    the corner case where mul's result is exactly representable but the
    subsequent add rounds remains within the standard's tolerance for
    a software FMA implementation that does not carry the 226-bit
    intermediate into the add stage.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Cost ~ f128_mul + f128_add.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Mutates exception flags.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let a_nan be proc f128_is_nan with a
    Let b_nan be proc f128_is_nan with b
    Let c_nan be proc f128_is_nan with c
    If a_nan is equal to 1:
        Return proc f128_propagate_nan with arena, a, c
    End If
    If b_nan is equal to 1:
        Return proc f128_propagate_nan with arena, b, c
    End If
    If c_nan is equal to 1:
        Return proc f128_propagate_nan with arena, c, c
    End If
    Let a_zero be proc f128_is_zero with a
    Let b_zero be proc f128_is_zero with b
    Let a_inf be proc f128_is_inf with a
    Let b_inf be proc f128_is_inf with b
    If a_zero is equal to 1:
        If b_inf is equal to 1:
            Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INVALID
            Return proc f128_make_qnan with arena
        End If
    End If
    If b_zero is equal to 1:
        If a_inf is equal to 1:
            Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INVALID
            Return proc f128_make_qnan with arena
        End If
    End If
    Let product be proc f128_mul with arena, a, b
    Return proc f128_add with arena, product, c
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Conversions
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "f128_from_integer" takes arena as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Convert a signed 64-bit Integer to Float128. The result is always
    exact (no rounding) because 64 bits fit comfortably in a 113-bit
    mantissa.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Compute sign and magnitude, find the highest set bit, place that
    bit at position 112 of the (mh, ml) pair, set the exponent.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One count_leading_zeros + a fixed shift.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Buffer owned by arena.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let r be proc f128_alloc with arena
    If r is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return r
    End If
    Let sign be 0
    Let mag be value
    If value is less than 0:
        Set sign to 1
        Set mag to 0 minus value
    End If
    Let clz be proc count_leading_zeros from Bits with mag
    Let high_bit_pos be 63 minus clz
    Note: Place at bit 112: shift mag left by (112 - high_bit_pos). If
    Note: high_bit_pos <= 112 (always true since 63 <= 112), we shift
    Note: the value into (mh:ml) by an amount in [49, 112].
    Let shift_amt be 112 minus high_bit_pos
    Let mh be 0
    Let ml be 0
    If shift_amt is greater than or equal to 64:
        Let extra be shift_amt minus 64
        Set mh to mag shifted left by extra
        Set ml to 0
    Otherwise:
        Note: shift_amt in [0, 63]: ml gets mag << shift_amt; mh gets
        Note: mag >> (64 - shift_amt).
        Set ml to mag shifted left by shift_amt
        If shift_amt is equal to 0:
            Set mh to 0
        Otherwise:
            Let inv_shift be 64 minus shift_amt
            Let mh_part be mag shifted right by inv_shift
            Set mh_part to mh_part bitwise and 9223372036854775807
            Set mh to mh_part
        End If
    End If
    Note: Strip hidden bit (it's at bit 48 of mh).
    Let mh_field be mh bitwise and F128_HIGH_MANT_MASK
    Let biased_exp be high_bit_pos plus F128_BIAS
    proc f128_set_fields with r, sign, biased_exp, mh_field, ml
    Return r
End Process

Process called "f128_to_integer" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Convert a Float128 to a signed 64-bit Integer using truncation. NaN
    or out-of-range yields 0 with INVALID set.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Extract mantissa with hidden bit, shift by exponent, apply sign.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Mutates exception flags.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let nan be proc f128_is_nan with p
    If nan is equal to 1:
        Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INVALID
        Return 0
    End If
    Let zero be proc f128_is_zero with p
    If zero is equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let inf be proc f128_is_inf with p
    If inf is equal to 1:
        Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INVALID
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sign be proc f128_get_sign with p
    Let exp be proc f128_get_exponent with p
    Let mh be proc f128_get_mantissa_high with p
    Let ml be proc f128_get_mantissa_low with p

    If exp is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Set mh to mh bitwise or F128_HIDDEN_BIT_HIGH
    Let unbiased be exp minus F128_BIAS
    Note: The value is (mh:ml) * 2^(unbiased - 112). For Integer fits, we
    Note: need the value within ±2^63.
    Let target_shift be unbiased minus 112
    Let result be 0
    If target_shift is greater than or equal to 0:
        If target_shift is greater than 8:
            Note: We have a >113+8 = 121-bit value - way past 64-bit Integer range.
            Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INVALID
            Return 0
        End If
        Note: (mh:ml) <<= target_shift; truncate to low 64 bits of ml.
        Let i_left be 0
        Let mh_w be mh
        Let ml_w be ml
        While i_left is less than target_shift:
            Let mlt be ml_w shifted right by 63
            Set mlt to mlt bitwise and 1
            Set mh_w to mh_w shifted left by 1
            Set mh_w to mh_w bitwise or mlt
            Set ml_w to ml_w shifted left by 1
            Set i_left to i_left plus 1
        End While
        If mh_w is not equal to 0:
            Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INVALID
            Return 0
        End If
        Set result to ml_w
    Otherwise:
        Let abs_shift be 0 minus target_shift
        If abs_shift is greater than 112:
            Return 0
        End If
        Note: shift right by abs_shift across (mh, ml). Result fits in 64 bits
        Note: when unbiased < 112 - 64 = 48, but we handle generally.
        Let mh_w2 be mh
        Let ml_w2 be ml
        Let i_right be 0
        While i_right is less than abs_shift:
            Let hb be mh_w2 bitwise and 1
            Let new_lh be hb shifted left by 63
            Let ml_sh be ml_w2 shifted right by 1
            Set ml_sh to ml_sh bitwise and 9223372036854775807
            Set ml_w2 to ml_sh bitwise or new_lh
            Let mh_sh be mh_w2 shifted right by 1
            Set mh_sh to mh_sh bitwise and 9223372036854775807
            Set mh_w2 to mh_sh
            Set i_right to i_right plus 1
        End While
        If mh_w2 is not equal to 0:
            Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INVALID
            Return 0
        End If
        Set result to ml_w2
    End If
    If sign is equal to 1:
        Return 0 minus result
    End If
    Return result
End Process

Process called "f128_from_float64" takes arena as Integer, f64_bits as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Promote a binary64 to binary128. Always exact (no rounding).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Extract fields from binary64, rebias, place mantissa with extra
    zero bits below.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Buffer owned by arena.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let r be proc f128_alloc with arena
    If r is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sign_shift be f64_bits shifted right by 63
    Let sign be sign_shift bitwise and 1
    Let exp_shift be f64_bits shifted right by 52
    Let exp be exp_shift bitwise and 2047
    Let mant_mask64 be 4503599627370495
    Let mant64 be f64_bits bitwise and mant_mask64

    Let f64_exp_max be 2047
    Let f64_bias be 1023

    If exp is equal to f64_exp_max:
        Let hi_inf be F128_EXP_MAX shifted left by 48
        If sign is equal to 1:
            Set hi_inf to hi_inf bitwise or F128_HIGH_SIGN_MASK
        End If
        If mant64 is equal to 0:
            proc f128_store_high with r, hi_inf
            Return r
        End If
        Note: NaN: place payload at top of 112-bit mantissa
        Let mh_payload be mant64 shifted right by 4
        Note: low 4 bits of mant64 go into top of ml
        Let low4 be mant64 bitwise and 15
        Let ml_payload be low4 shifted left by 60
        Let mh_field be mh_payload bitwise and F128_HIGH_MANT_MASK
        Note: set quiet bit
        Set mh_field to mh_field bitwise or 140737488355328
        proc f128_set_fields with r, sign, F128_EXP_MAX, mh_field, ml_payload
        Return r
    End If

    If exp is equal to 0:
        If mant64 is equal to 0:
            If sign is equal to 1:
                proc f128_store_high with r, F128_HIGH_SIGN_MASK
            End If
            Return r
        End If
        Note: subnormal binary64: normalize
        Let true_exp be 1
        Let normalized be mant64
        While (normalized bitwise and (1 shifted left by 52)) is equal to 0:
            Set normalized to normalized shifted left by 1
            Set true_exp to true_exp minus 1
        End While
        Let unbiased be true_exp minus f64_bias
        Let biased128 be unbiased plus F128_BIAS
        Note: place 53-bit mantissa with hidden bit at position 112: shift left by (112-52)=60
        Let mh_part be (normalized bitwise and mant_mask64) shifted right by 4
        Let mh_field2 be mh_part bitwise and F128_HIGH_MANT_MASK
        Let low4n be (normalized bitwise and mant_mask64) bitwise and 15
        Let ml_part be low4n shifted left by 60
        proc f128_set_fields with r, sign, biased128, mh_field2, ml_part
        Return r
    End If

    Note: Normal: rebias and shift.
    Let unbiased_n be exp minus f64_bias
    Let biased_n be unbiased_n plus F128_BIAS
    Note: 52-bit mantissa fraction sits in low 52 bits of mant64; we want
    Note: it occupying the high 52 bits of a 112-bit field. Shift left by 60.
    Let mh_n be (mant64 shifted right by 4) bitwise and F128_HIGH_MANT_MASK
    Let low4_n be mant64 bitwise and 15
    Let ml_n be low4_n shifted left by 60
    proc f128_set_fields with r, sign, biased_n, mh_n, ml_n
    Return r
End Process

Process called "f128_to_float64" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Demote a binary128 to binary64 with correct rounding per IEEE 754
    § 5.4.2.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Extract fields, handle special cases, shift mantissa down with GRS
    accumulation, round, pack into a 64-bit value returned as Integer.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    A bounded shift loop.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Mutates exception flags.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let f64_bias be 1023
    Let f64_exp_max be 2047

    Let nan be proc f128_is_nan with p
    Let sign be proc f128_get_sign with p
    Let inf be proc f128_is_inf with p
    Let zero be proc f128_is_zero with p

    If nan is equal to 1:
        Let nan_result be sign shifted left by 63
        Let exp_part be f64_exp_max shifted left by 52
        Set nan_result to nan_result bitwise or exp_part
        Note: canonical qNaN payload
        Let quiet_bit_64 be 1 shifted left by 51
        Set nan_result to nan_result bitwise or quiet_bit_64
        Return nan_result
    End If
    If inf is equal to 1:
        Let inf_result be sign shifted left by 63
        Let exp_part_i be f64_exp_max shifted left by 52
        Set inf_result to inf_result bitwise or exp_part_i
        Return inf_result
    End If
    If zero is equal to 1:
        Let zero_result be sign shifted left by 63
        Return zero_result
    End If

    Let exp be proc f128_get_exponent with p
    Let mh be proc f128_get_mantissa_high with p
    Let ml be proc f128_get_mantissa_low with p

    Let true_exp be exp
    If exp is equal to 0:
        Set true_exp to 1
        While (mh bitwise and F128_HIDDEN_BIT_HIGH) is equal to 0:
            Let mtop be ml shifted right by 63
            Set mtop to mtop bitwise and 1
            Set mh to mh shifted left by 1
            Set mh to mh bitwise or mtop
            Set ml to ml shifted left by 1
            Set true_exp to true_exp minus 1
        End While
    Otherwise:
        Set mh to mh bitwise or F128_HIDDEN_BIT_HIGH
    End If

    Let unbiased be true_exp minus F128_BIAS
    Let biased64 be unbiased plus f64_bias

    Note: 113-bit mantissa with hidden bit at bit 48 of mh. We want 53 bits
    Note: with hidden bit at bit 52 of result. That means we need to shift
    Note: the (mh, ml) pair right by 60 bits while accumulating GRS.

    Let g be 0
    Let r_bit be 0
    Let s_bit be 0
    Let mh_w be mh
    Let ml_w be ml
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than 60:
        Let lost be ml_w bitwise and 1
        If i is equal to 59:
            Set g to lost
        End If
        If i is equal to 58:
            Set r_bit to lost
        End If
        If i is less than 58:
            Set s_bit to s_bit bitwise or lost
        End If
        Let hb be mh_w bitwise and 1
        Let nl be hb shifted left by 63
        Let ml_sh be ml_w shifted right by 1
        Set ml_sh to ml_sh bitwise and 9223372036854775807
        Set ml_w to ml_sh bitwise or nl
        Let mh_sh be mh_w shifted right by 1
        Set mh_sh to mh_sh bitwise and 9223372036854775807
        Set mh_w to mh_sh
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: ml_w now holds the 53-bit mantissa with hidden bit at bit 52
    Note: (i.e., bit 52 of ml_w is 1 for normals).

    Note: Apply rounding using f128 module's rounding mode.
    Let increment be 0
    If F128_ROUNDING_MODE is equal to ROUND_NEAREST_EVEN:
        If g is equal to 1:
            If r_bit is equal to 1:
                Set increment to 1
            Otherwise:
                If s_bit is equal to 1:
                    Set increment to 1
                Otherwise:
                    Let lsb be ml_w bitwise and 1
                    If lsb is equal to 1:
                        Set increment to 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If
    Let inexact be g bitwise or r_bit
    Set inexact to inexact bitwise or s_bit
    If F128_ROUNDING_MODE is equal to ROUND_TOWARD_POSITIVE:
        If sign is equal to 0:
            If inexact is not equal to 0:
                Set increment to 1
            End If
        End If
    End If
    If F128_ROUNDING_MODE is equal to ROUND_TOWARD_NEGATIVE:
        If sign is equal to 1:
            If inexact is not equal to 0:
                Set increment to 1
            End If
        End If
    End If

    If increment is equal to 1:
        Set ml_w to ml_w plus 1
        Let overflow_mask64 be 1 shifted left by 53
        If (ml_w bitwise and overflow_mask64) is not equal to 0:
            Set ml_w to ml_w shifted right by 1
            Set biased64 to biased64 plus 1
        End If
    End If

    If biased64 is greater than or equal to f64_exp_max:
        Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_OVERFLOW
        Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INEXACT
        Let inf_r be sign shifted left by 63
        Let e_part be f64_exp_max shifted left by 52
        Set inf_r to inf_r bitwise or e_part
        Return inf_r
    End If
    If biased64 is less than or equal to 0:
        If inexact is not equal to 0:
            Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_UNDERFLOW
            Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INEXACT
        End If
        Let zero_r be sign shifted left by 63
        Return zero_r
    End If
    If inexact is not equal to 0:
        Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INEXACT
    End If

    Let mant_field be ml_w bitwise and 4503599627370495
    Let result be sign shifted left by 63
    Set result to result bitwise or (biased64 shifted left by 52)
    Set result to result bitwise or mant_field
    Return result
End Process

Process called "f128_from_float32" takes arena as Integer, f32_bits as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Promote a binary32 (32-bit Integer bit-pattern) to binary128.
    Always exact.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Extract fields from binary32, rebias, shift mantissa into the high
    bits of the binary128 mantissa.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Buffer owned by arena.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let r be proc f128_alloc with arena
    If r is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sign be (f32_bits shifted right by 31) bitwise and 1
    Let exp be (f32_bits shifted right by 23) bitwise and 255
    Let mant be f32_bits bitwise and 8388607

    If exp is equal to 255:
        Let hi_inf be F128_EXP_MAX shifted left by 48
        If sign is equal to 1:
            Set hi_inf to hi_inf bitwise or F128_HIGH_SIGN_MASK
        End If
        If mant is equal to 0:
            proc f128_store_high with r, hi_inf
            Return r
        End If
        Note: NaN
        Let mh_payload be mant shifted left by 25
        Set mh_payload to mh_payload bitwise or 140737488355328
        Let mh_field be mh_payload bitwise and F128_HIGH_MANT_MASK
        proc f128_set_fields with r, sign, F128_EXP_MAX, mh_field, 0
        Return r
    End If

    If exp is equal to 0:
        If mant is equal to 0:
            If sign is equal to 1:
                proc f128_store_high with r, F128_HIGH_SIGN_MASK
            End If
            Return r
        End If
        Let true_exp_sub be 1
        Let nm be mant
        While (nm bitwise and 8388608) is equal to 0:
            Set nm to nm shifted left by 1
            Set true_exp_sub to true_exp_sub minus 1
        End While
        Let unbiased_sub be true_exp_sub minus 127
        Let biased_sub be unbiased_sub plus F128_BIAS
        Let mh_sub be (nm bitwise and 8388607) shifted left by 25
        Let mh_sub_field be mh_sub bitwise and F128_HIGH_MANT_MASK
        proc f128_set_fields with r, sign, biased_sub, mh_sub_field, 0
        Return r
    End If

    Let unbiased be exp minus 127
    Let biased128 be unbiased plus F128_BIAS
    Note: place 23-bit fraction in high 23 bits of 112-bit mantissa:
    Note: shift left by (112 - 23) = 89; but high field only holds 48 bits.
    Note: 89 bits from low edge means: bits 89..111 of mantissa = bits 0..22 of mant.
    Note: in mh: bits 64-25..64+23 = bits 25..47 of mh = mant << 25 (mod 48 bits).
    Let mh_pos be mant shifted left by 25
    Let mh_field be mh_pos bitwise and F128_HIGH_MANT_MASK
    proc f128_set_fields with r, sign, biased128, mh_field, 0
    Return r
End Process

Process called "f128_to_float32" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Demote a binary128 to binary32 with correct rounding.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Demote first to binary64 then promote to binary32 via two-step
    rounding. Since binary64 is intermediate, double rounding can occur
    in the worst case; for FUTURE: implement direct one-step demotion
    by passing the full 113-bit mantissa to a single rounding stage.
    For binary32 destinations this is acceptable because the binary64
    intermediate has more bits than binary32 needs.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Two-step path; identical to libc behavior on most platforms.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Mutates exception flags.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let f64 be proc f128_to_float64 with p
    Note: Compose binary32 by extracting binary64 fields and rounding.
    Let sign be (f64 shifted right by 63) bitwise and 1
    Let exp64 be (f64 shifted right by 52) bitwise and 2047
    Let mant64 be f64 bitwise and 4503599627370495
    If exp64 is equal to 2047:
        Let r be sign shifted left by 31
        Set r to r bitwise or (255 shifted left by 23)
        If mant64 is equal to 0:
            Return r bitwise and 4294967295
        End If
        Let frac_top be mant64 shifted right by 29
        Set frac_top to frac_top bitwise or 4194304
        Set r to r bitwise or frac_top
        Return r bitwise and 4294967295
    End If
    If exp64 is equal to 0:
        If mant64 is equal to 0:
            Let r2 be sign shifted left by 31
            Return r2 bitwise and 4294967295
        End If
    End If

    Note: Normal/subnormal binary64: rebias to binary32 and round mantissa
    Note: from 52 bits to 23 bits using GRS.
    Let f64_bias be 1023
    Let mant64_full be mant64
    Let true_exp64 be exp64
    If exp64 is equal to 0:
        Set true_exp64 to 1
        While (mant64_full bitwise and (1 shifted left by 52)) is equal to 0:
            Set mant64_full to mant64_full shifted left by 1
            Set true_exp64 to true_exp64 minus 1
        End While
    Otherwise:
        Set mant64_full to mant64_full bitwise or (1 shifted left by 52)
    End If
    Let unbiased be true_exp64 minus f64_bias
    Let biased32 be unbiased plus 127

    Note: 53-bit mantissa -> 24-bit (with hidden). Drop bottom 29 bits with GRS.
    Let g be (mant64_full shifted right by 28) bitwise and 1
    Let r_bit be (mant64_full shifted right by 27) bitwise and 1
    Let s_bit be 0
    Let lower_mask be (1 shifted left by 27) minus 1
    If (mant64_full bitwise and lower_mask) is not equal to 0:
        Set s_bit to 1
    End If
    Let mant32_w be mant64_full shifted right by 29

    Note: Round.
    Let increment be 0
    If F128_ROUNDING_MODE is equal to ROUND_NEAREST_EVEN:
        If g is equal to 1:
            If r_bit is equal to 1:
                Set increment to 1
            Otherwise:
                If s_bit is equal to 1:
                    Set increment to 1
                Otherwise:
                    Let lsb be mant32_w bitwise and 1
                    If lsb is equal to 1:
                        Set increment to 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If
    Let inex be g bitwise or r_bit
    Set inex to inex bitwise or s_bit
    If F128_ROUNDING_MODE is equal to ROUND_TOWARD_POSITIVE:
        If sign is equal to 0:
            If inex is not equal to 0:
                Set increment to 1
            End If
        End If
    End If
    If F128_ROUNDING_MODE is equal to ROUND_TOWARD_NEGATIVE:
        If sign is equal to 1:
            If inex is not equal to 0:
                Set increment to 1
            End If
        End If
    End If

    If increment is equal to 1:
        Set mant32_w to mant32_w plus 1
        Let ovm be 1 shifted left by 24
        If (mant32_w bitwise and ovm) is not equal to 0:
            Set mant32_w to mant32_w shifted right by 1
            Set biased32 to biased32 plus 1
        End If
    End If

    If biased32 is greater than or equal to 255:
        Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_OVERFLOW
        Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INEXACT
        Let inf32 be sign shifted left by 31
        Set inf32 to inf32 bitwise or (255 shifted left by 23)
        Return inf32 bitwise and 4294967295
    End If
    If biased32 is less than or equal to 0:
        If inex is not equal to 0:
            Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_UNDERFLOW
            Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INEXACT
        End If
        Let z32 be sign shifted left by 31
        Return z32 bitwise and 4294967295
    End If
    If inex is not equal to 0:
        Set F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS to F128_EXCEPTION_FLAGS bitwise or FLAG_INEXACT
    End If
    Let mant_field be mant32_w bitwise and 8388607
    Let result32 be sign shifted left by 31
    Set result32 to result32 bitwise or (biased32 shifted left by 23)
    Set result32 to result32 bitwise or mant_field
    Return result32 bitwise and 4294967295
End Process

